article.headline: New Orleans 66, Jacksonville State 54
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored 23 points and New Orleans held off a second-half Jacksonville State rally to win 66-54 on Saturday. McCalebb, who's averaging 23 points, hit 9-of-21 shots, grabbed nine rebounds and had five assists. Jamie McNeilly added 13 points on 5-of-8 shooting while Joey Barnitz scored 11 points for New Orleans (1-2). Courtney Bradley had 17 points and eight rebounds for JSU (0-1). New Orleans went on an 18-0 run during an eight-minute stretch in the first half. McNeilly had all of his seven first-half points during that spurt to help New Orleans take a 35-16 lead at the half. The Gamecocks outscored New Orleans 28-10 in the first 11 minutes of the second half and got as close as 45-44 on a pair of Bradley free throws with 9:26 left. But McCalebb scored the next six points, and the Privateers led by at least six points for the rest of the game.
